{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2c6c3047-5af4-43fd-9062-62fd0455a15b","content":"The directory is empty — no existing files to convert. Here's exactly what you need:\n\n## Compiled Bindings with `x:DataType`\n\nAdd the `x:DataType` attribute to your `ContentPage` (or any element that sets a `BindingContext`), pointing at your ViewModel's CLR type:\n\n```xml\n<!-- SettingsPage.xaml -->\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n    xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n    xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n    x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n    x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"Theme\" />\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Notifications\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Font Size\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"72\" Increment=\"1\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only change** vs. a plain-binding page is adding:\n1. The `xmlns:vm` namespace import for your ViewModel.\n2. `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `ContentPage`.\n\nEvery `{Binding}` inside that scope is now **compiled** — the XAML compiler resolves property names against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit build errors for typos (e.g., `{Binding Themee}` → **XC0045: property not found**). To make this stricter project-wide, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding warnings as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `XC0045` | Property not found on the `x:DataType` type |\n| `XC0022` | No `x:DataType` set (uncompiled binding) |\n\n### Tips\n- **Scoping**: `x:DataType` is inherited by child elements. If a child has a different `BindingContext`, set a new `x:DataType` there.\n- **Opt out locally**: Use `x:DataType=\"\"` on a subtree that must stay reflection-based (e.g., bindings to `x:Reference`).\n- With `WarningsAsErrors` for `XC0022`, the build will fail any time someone adds a binding without `x:DataType`, preventing regressions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8098dbbe-eaf1-4681-b05d-ccea1039e9f3","outputTokens":728,"requestId":"1030:16EA54:155415D:17E4DE3:69FD3380"},"id":"1951e90a-08af-4a2d-b88c-e8e790a0a9c3","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:27.918Z","parentId":"c26d3a2f-4e7e-41c0-8d14-94ca21b80b33"}
